1. What is SQL?
Definition

SQL (Structured Query Language) is a standard language used to create, access, modify, and manage data stored in relational databases.

It is used to:

Create databases and tables
Insert data
Retrieve data
Update data
Delete data
Basic Syntax
SELECT column_name
FROM table_name;
Example
SELECT * FROM Students;

Output

StudentID	Name	Age
101	Rahul	20
102	Priya	21
2. What are Databases?
Definition

A database is an organized collection of related data that can be stored, managed, and accessed efficiently.

Example:

Student records
Employee details
Bank accounts
Hospital records
Syntax
CREATE DATABASE database_name;
Example
CREATE DATABASE College;

This creates a database named College.

